{"id":285,"parent_id":277,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":285,"title":"2 Samuel 8","subtitle":"","short_title":"2 Sam.","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 8"],[".studySummary",["i","David defeats and subjects many nations—The Lord is with him—He executes judgment and justice unto all his people."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.1","order":"02.11.008.22843"},["b","1"],"And after this it came to pass, that David",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"smote"],"the Philistines, and subdued them: and David took Metheg-ammah out of the hand of the Philistines."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.2","order":"02.11.008.22844"},["b","2"],"And he smote",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_2a"},"Moab"],", and",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_2b"},"measured"],"them with a line, casting them down to the ground; even with two lines measured he to put to death, and with one full line to keep alive. And",["i","so"],"the",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_2c"},"Moabites"],"became David’s servants,",["i","and"],"brought gifts."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.3","order":"02.11.008.22845"},["b","3"],"¶David smote also Hadadezer, the son of Rehob, king of Zobah, as he went to recover his border at the river Euphrates."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.4","order":"02.11.008.22846"},["b","4"],"And David took from him a thousand",["i","chariots,"],"and seven hundred horsemen, and twenty thousand footmen: and David houghed all the chariot",["i","horses,"],"but reserved of them",["i","for"],"an hundred chariots."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.5","order":"02.11.008.22847"},["b","5"],"And when the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"Syrians"],"of Damascus came to succour Hadadezer king of Zobah, David slew of the Syrians two and twenty thousand men."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.6","order":"02.11.008.22848"},["b","6"],"Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus: and the Syrians became servants to David,",["i","and"],"brought gifts. And the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"preserved David whithersoever he went."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.7","order":"02.11.008.22849"},["b","7"],"And David took the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_7a"},"shields"],"of gold that were on the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.8","order":"02.11.008.22850"},["b","8"],"And from Betah, and from Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, king David took exceeding much brass."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.9","order":"02.11.008.22851"},["b","9"],"¶When Toi king of Hamath heard that David had smitten all the host of Hadadezer,"],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.10","order":"02.11.008.22852"},["b","10"],"Then Toi sent Joram his son unto king David, to salute him, and to bless him, because he had fought against Hadadezer, and smitten him: for Hadadezer had wars with Toi. And",["i","Joram"],"brought with him vessels of silver, and vessels of gold, and vessels of brass:"],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.11","order":"02.11.008.22853"},["b","11"],"Which also king David did",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_11a"},"dedicate"],"unto the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", with the silver and gold that he had dedicated of all nations which he subdued;"],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.12","order":"02.11.008.22854"},["b","12"],"Of Syria, and of Moab, and of the children of",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_12a"},"Ammon"],", and of the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_12b"},"Philistines"],", and of",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_12c"},"Amalek"],", and of the spoil of Hadadezer, son of Rehob, king of Zobah."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.13","order":"02.11.008.22855"},["b","13"],"And David gat",["i","him"],"a name when he returned from smiting of the Syrians in the valley of",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_13a"},"salt"],",",["i","being"],"eighteen thousand",["i","men."]],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.14","order":"02.11.008.22856"},["b","14"],"¶And he put garrisons in Edom; throughout all Edom put he garrisons, and all they of",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_14a"},"Edom"],"became David’s servants. And the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"preserved David whithersoever he went."],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.15","order":"02.11.008.22857"},["b","15"],"And David",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_15a"},"reigned"],"over all Israel; and David executed judgment and justice unto all his people."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.16","order":"02.11.008.22858"},["b","16"],"And",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_16a"},"Joab"],"the son of Zeruiah",["i","was"],"over the host; and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud",["i","was"],"recorder;"],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.17","order":"02.11.008.22859"},["b","17"],"And",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_17a"},"Zadok"],"the son of Ahitub, and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar,",["i","were"],"the priests; and Seraiah",["i","was"],"the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_17b"},"scribe"],";"],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.18","order":"02.11.008.22860"},["b","18"],"And",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_18a"},"Benaiah"],"the son of Jehoiada",["i","was over"],"both the Cherethites and the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_18b"},"Pelethites"],"; and David’s sons were",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_18c"},"chief rulers"],"."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.1a","order":"02.11.008.22861"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/18.1.1-17"},"1 Chr. 18:1 (1–17)"],"."],["div",{"id":"2a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.2a","order":"02.11.008.22863"},["b","2a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/24.17"},"Num. 24:17"],"."],["div",{"id":"2b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.2b","order":"02.11.008.22865"},["b","2b"],["span.small","IE"],"He apparently determined their size and put the taller, stronger to death."],["div",{"id":"2c","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.2c","order":"02.11.008.22867"},["b","2c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/1.1"},"2 Kgs. 1:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/3.5"},"3:5"],"."],["div",{"id":"5a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.5a","order":"02.11.008.22869"},["b","5a"],["span.small","HEB"],"Aram; i.e., Arameans. They were later called “Syrians” by Greek peoples."],["div",{"id":"7a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.7a","order":"02.11.008.22871"},["b","7a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/11.10"},"2 Kgs. 11:10"],"."],["div",{"id":"11a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.11a","order":"02.11.008.22873"},["b","11a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/7.51"},"1 Kgs. 7:51"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/26.27.26-27"},"1 Chr. 26:27 (26–27)"],"."],["div",{"id":"12a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.12a","order":"02.11.008.22875"},["b","12a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/10.14.6-14"},"2 Sam. 10:14 (6–14)"],"."],["div",{"id":"12b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.12b","order":"02.11.008.22877"},["b","12b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/5.25.17-25"},"2 Sam. 5:25 (17–25)"],"."],["div",{"id":"12c","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.12c","order":"02.11.008.22879"},["b","12c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/17.14"},"Ex. 17:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/30.18.1-20"},"1 Sam. 30:18 (1–20)"],"."],["div",{"id":"13a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.13a","order":"02.11.008.22881"},["b","13a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/14.7"},"2 Kgs. 14:7"],"."],["div",{"id":"14a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.14a","order":"02.11.008.22883"},["b","14a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/27.37.29-40"},"Gen. 27:37 (29–40)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/24.18"},"Num. 24:18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/3.9"},"2 Kgs. 3:9"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/60.8"},"Ps. 60:8"],"."],["div",{"id":"15a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.15a","order":"02.11.008.22885"},["b","15a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/5.4"},"2 Sam. 5:4"],"."],["div",{"id":"16a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.16a","order":"02.11.008.22887"},["b","16a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/20.23.23-26"},"2 Sam. 20:23 (23–26)"],"."],["div",{"id":"17a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.17a","order":"02.11.008.22889"},["b","17a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/15.24"},"2 Sam. 15:24"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/2.35"},"1 Kgs. 2:35"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/6.8"},"1 Chr. 6:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/24.3"},"24:3"],"."],["div",{"id":"17b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.17b","order":"02.11.008.22891"},["b","17b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/scribe"},"TG Scribe"],"."],["div",{"id":"18a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.18a","order":"02.11.008.22893"},["b","18a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/2.25"},"1 Kgs. 2:25"],"."],["div",{"id":"18b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.18b","order":"02.11.008.22895"},["b","18b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/1.38"},"1 Kgs. 1:38"],"."],["div",{"id":"18c","uri":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.18c","order":"02.11.008.22897"},["b","18c"],["span.small","HEB"],"priests; apparently, in this case, civil ministers."]]}
